title: S.J. boys and girls: Eastern edges Lenape
text:
Tri-County Classic. Annie Sanker scored two goals and Emily Glavin scored once for Pitman to defeat host Pennsville, 3-2.
Tri-County Royal. Hammonton's Madison Chiola scored the lone goal in a 1-0 win at Highland. 
Ashley Enger and Mary Kate Ulmer each scored twice, and Williamstown beat visiting Clearview, 7-2. 
Cape-Atlantic League. Abby Daigle scored three goals for host Millville to help defeat Vineland, 4-1. Amber Raines also scored and had an assist. Boys' Soccer Luke Berenato scored for Gateway in a 1-0 win over visiting Haddon Township in Colonial Conference Play.
Tri-County Diamond. Tyler Lunsford and Jake Puglia each scored for Schalick at home in a 2-1 win against Penns Grove. 
Hunter Briggs, Kris Hartung and Jon Torres each had a goal to give host Glassboro a 3-1 win over Deptford. 
Tri-County Royal. Kyle Uzdavines scored the only goal for Williamstown against host Clearview in the 1-0 win. 
Doug Gant scored to give Delsea a 1-0 win over host Kingsway. Field Hockey Mackenzie Keegan scored four goals in Eastern's 11-0 win over host Lenape in an Olympic Conference match. Madison Morano had two goals and three assists.
Tri-County Classic. Olivia Amwake scored three goals in a 5-0 win for Pitman over visiting Pennsville. 
Tri-County Diamond. Woodstown's Tori Gatanis scored against Cumberland in a 1-1 tie at home. Gillian Nardelli had the goal for Cumberland. Baseball Millville junior third baseman Buddy Kennedy orally committed to the University of North Carolina. Kennedy was first team all-Cape Atlantic and named to the Carpenter Cup team as a sophomore.
